Energy Industry Professional:
 
Global Change Associates and the MYA Group announce the "Green Trading Summit. " This is first conference attacking the triple convergence of the new markets of emissions, renewables and negawatt trading in a risk management context. The conference will be held in New York City on May 14 & 15 at the McGraw-Hill Building in midtown Manhattan. Topics include SO2, NOX, and CO2 trading as well as renewable energy credit and negawatt (energy efficiency) trading. Learn about how t o create environmental indexes for trading, establishing the forward curve for environmental products applying environmental trading for project finance in this emerging commodity market.
 
Speakers from Rocky Mountain Institute, Green-e, Fannie Mae, Sterling Planet, Evolutions Markets, EcoSecurities, the Automated Power Exchange, Duane Morris LLP, Dow Jones, the Demand Exchange, and the Chicago Climate Exchange are participating at this ground breaking event.
 
